<br>
Generally after fighting two blues, I'm down to less than two bubbles of mana and down a bubble or two in health.  Clarity helps quite a bit, but I usually can't depend on having a friendly 'Chanter within arm's reach while I solo, not to mention also wanting a SoW (I can't afford to use up SoW potions all of the time).  <br>
<br>
I'm a 33rd level Mage and my int is not too shabby at 190 and I have an additional 60 mana from gear (total mana is 1380).  My usual tactic is to DS the pet (Water pet and I summon swords and give it Burnout II), then pull the mob with either Malaise or Shock of Spikes.  I then usually let the pet build up aggro before I stand and cast more shocks (two or three more usually) till it starts to run, then I let the pet melee while I smack it with my mug (saving mana).<br>
<br>
I then loot the corpse for my usual 6sp, 12cp and a Tump Stump then it's time to med for five minutes.  I know I could use an Earth pet, but I haven't found that the root sticks all that often (that was pre 29th with the 24th Earth pet, I failed twice at the 29th Earth pet and was out of gloves).  Maybe things will improve when I get my spanking new 34th level focused pets, but in the past I have always found that soloing was wrought with downtime.<br>
<br>
So am I doing something wrong (boy, that's asking for it!)?  Are your experiences similar?  What tactics do you use?  Thanks for your feedback.<br>
 <p><img src="http://members.bellatlantic.net/~tabb/XtalName1.jpg">
<BR>Xtal Matrix / Magician of the 32nd Exploding Penguin
<BR><b><i>-Quezzy-</i></b> / Half-Elven Ranger of the 20th Season 
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubalasmage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BalasMage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#333333>(3/28/01 4:34:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=179.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Soloing Mage Tactics</span><hr size=1> nope you doin fine it sounds like.  that is just the sucky part of soloing as a mage.  downtime with no extra mana regen like necros.  Malise pull, pet gets the taunt up, and nuke it down.  or you can heal pet but i usually just chain cast another rather then healing.  at 33 my reccomendation would be grouping at the FM zone in OT. xp just flies there on my server.  I'm 45 now and can solo but don't.  To much downtime and medding medding medding if i solo.  Course if you got a good book it ain't that bad =P hope this helps.<br>
